@clientRegression
Feature: Client Page Functionality

Scenario: Verify Client page loads successfully
  Given user is logged in
  When user navigates to Client page
  Then Client page header should be displayed
  And Client table should be displayed

Scenario: Verify Client page header
  Given user is on Client page
  Then page header should display "Client"

Scenario: Verify client table headers
  Given user is on Client page
  Then following columns should be displayed
    | S.No |
    | Date |
    | Company Name |
    | Email |
    | Status |
    | Service Details |
    | Action |

Scenario: Verify client records are displayed
  Given user is on Client page
  Then at least one client record should be displayed

Scenario: Verify Add New Client button visibility
  Given user is on Client page
  Then Add New Client button should be displayed

Scenario: Verify Add New Client functionality
  Given user is on Client page
  When user clicks Add New Client button
  Then Add Client popup should be displayed

Scenario: Verify Filter button visibility
  Given user is on Client page
  Then Filter button should be displayed

Scenario: Verify filter popup opens
  Given user is on Client page
  When user clicks Filter button
  Then Filter popup should be displayed

Scenario Outline: Verify client search
  Given user is on Client page
  When user searches company "<CompanyName>"
  Then matching company should be displayed

Examples:
| CompanyName         |
| RHINOTECH_PVT_LTD   |
| CASHTEZ_PVT_LTD     |

Scenario: Verify status toggle displayed
  Given user is on Client page
  Then status toggle should be displayed for every client

Scenario: Verify client status can be changed
  Given user is on Client page
  When user changes client status
  Then status should be updated successfully

Scenario: Verify SP Details button
  Given user is on Client page
  Then SP Details button should be displayed

Scenario: Verify SP Details page opens
  Given user is on Client page
  When user clicks SP Details button
  Then Service Provider Details page should be displayed

Scenario: Verify action menu visibility
  Given user is on Client page
  Then action menu icon should be displayed

Scenario: Verify action menu opens
  Given user is on Client page
  When user clicks action menu
  Then action options should be displayed

Scenario: Verify client edit functionality
  Given user is on Client page
  When user selects Edit option
  Then Edit Client popup should be displayed

Scenario: Verify client details view
  Given user is on Client page
  When user clicks View option
  Then client details should be displayed

Scenario: Verify pagination controls
  Given user is on Client page
  Then pagination should be displayed

Scenario: Verify next page navigation
  Given user is on Client page
  When user clicks next page button
  Then next page should be displayed

Scenario: Verify previous page navigation
  Given user is on page 2
  When user clicks previous page button
  Then page 1 should be displayed

Scenario: Verify direct page navigation
  Given user is on Client page
  When user clicks page number 2
  Then page 2 data should be displayed

Scenario: Verify page size functionality
  Given user is on Client page
  When user enters page size 20
  Then 20 records should be displayed

Scenario: Verify serial numbers
  Given user is on Client page
  Then serial numbers should be displayed sequentially

Scenario: Verify client email format
  Given user is on Client page
  Then displayed email addresses should be valid

Scenario: Verify client date format
  Given user is on Client page
  Then dates should be displayed in valid format

Scenario: Verify logout button visibility
  Given user is on Client page
  Then logout button should be displayed

Scenario: Verify logout functionality
  Given user is on Client page
  When user clicks logout button
  Then user should navigate to login page
  
  
  
1. Login
2. Navigate to Client Page
3. Verify Client Header
4. Verify Client Records Displayed
5. Verify Add New Client Button
6. Verify Filter Button
7. Verify SP Details Button
8. Verify Action Menu
9. Verify Pagination
10. Logout